An unusual possession of the ancient great hunter.
Whatever magic used to enchant this shield is long gone, though it retains its excellent craftsmanship.
Immense shield that is quite heavy, but that protects from arrows aimed for the wielder’s head or legs.
Shield used by the Wolf-Knights of the northern reaches, who brave the bitter cold to stop the spread of icy beasts.
The added fangs do little to improve the shield’s toughness, but are telling of the wielder’s mental state.
Peculiar oval shield used by the warriors of an ancient legion.

Hastily built from broken planks, it grants the ability to block arrows, at least.
This shield is unlikely to last long in a fight.
A shield made long ago to be ornamental, due to its weight, but that is still useful in combat.
A shield that has been masterfully made, being meant for guards within a ruler’s inner circle.

A shield seldom used by a lich minions, as they have no regard for their life.
Mortal agents can be rewarded with this equipment, however.
Shield depicting a fictional creature of great power; one that is common in street theatre and children’s books.

Blood-red shield used by the leaders of northern tribes.
Its bold color makes it stand out in the snowy landscape.
Common but high-quality shield used by warriors of the desert.

Specially grown fungus used by Troglodytes as offerings to their queen-goddess.
It makes for a surprisingly usable shield.
Monstrous shield best used in a deadly combination with a one-handed axe also made of chitin.
Depicting a sun, this shield is praised for its high durability.
“Sometimes, it’s not about power, it’s about style.”
Morbid shield made by the deranged gravekeeper Cremeuh, to reward you for robbing graves.
Shield of the highest quality, beset with a Tsar Stone that gently emits green light.
“On the festival’s first day, we celebrate the spirit of honor.”
“On the festival’s second day, we bow to the spirit of perseverance.”
“On the festival’s third day, we cower before the spirit of death.”
“On the festival’s last day, we shun the spirit of hunger.”
Sensual clothes that enable one to dance, or fight, without end.
Sensual clothes that enable one to dance, or fight, without end.
Sensual clothes that enable one to dance, or fight, without end.
Sensual mask that enables one to dance, or fight, without end.
Sensual leggings that enable one to dance, or fight, without end.
Strange mask that makes one want to run fast and caw loudly.
Like other survival attires, this improvised coat has additional pockets.
“When calling the kettle black just wasn’t enough.”
A bizarre illusory costume of a legendary skeleton adventurer.
ooo_row.column_6: “Can’t feel em’ weathers, and it’s got lots o’ storage space!”

ooo_row.column_3: A bizarre illusory costume of a legendary skeleton adventurer.

ooo_row.column_3:
Common berry that only offers a small amount of nutrition and will quickly rot unless cooked.
As a fruit, these berries restore stamina over time.
Poisonous seed that, when grilled, is the first step in creating usable poisons.
Bulbous root vegetable with mana-restoring properties.

Edible meat that should be cooked first, as it rots quickly and carries diseases while raw.
As a type of meat, this food restores health over time.
Potent meat from prime animals, which rots quickly and carries diseases while raw.

Eggs of exotic insects, with diverse restorative capacities.
Eating it raw carries a chance of disease.
Rare crustacean coveted by fishermen for its mana-restoring qualities but that can make one ill when eaten raw.

Shimmering fish that restores mana but that can make one ill when eaten raw.
It also increases your resistance to all elemental damage.

Common fish that is edible raw but rots quickly and can make one ill.
Fish and seafood have mana-restoring properties, and are quite important in a mage’s diet.
Peculiar toadstool that gives headaches when eaten raw, but is an ingredient in health-restoring elixirs.
Celestial toadstool which restores mana and is an ingredient in magic-restoring elixirs.

Heavy marsh fruit that restore far more stamina than Gaberries.
These raw melons gain anti-poison properties when boiled.
Heavy desert fruit that re-invigorates and protects against the sun.

Uncommon reinvigorating insect that lives in plants and is used in advanced recipes.
Eating this insect protect from the cold.
Scarab, found in mineral ores, whose resin hardens one’s body from Impacts.
Bland mushroom which restores little hunger, often found in dank caves.

Large Pearlbird egg that carries a chance of disease when eaten raw.
Eggs provide both health and stamina recovery over time.
Airy mushroom strands that, when eaten, muffle the sound of one’s footsteps.

Rare marsh octopus, which closes wounds but poisons the eater.
It also instantly cures infections.
Iridescent flesh of a rare bird which increases one’s movement speed.
Fire-infused plant that grows in burnt lands.
Edible nut that is a main ingredient in stamina-restoring elixirs.
Diseased mush that is what remains when a cooking recipe fails.
Slab of meat grilled over a campfire, removing any risk of disease.
Piece of very nutritious and fortifying meat.
Salted meat that rots very slowly.
Salted alpha meat that rots very slowly, while retaining the special meat’s qualities.
Combined bread and alpha meat, which keep the meat’s combat-enhancing properties.
Crushed berries boiled into nutritious syrup, with warming properties.
Fish cooked over a campfire, removing any risk of disease.

Highly prized fish filet that shimmers brightly.
It restores mana and increases your resistance against elemental damage.
Basic food that can be bought in any city, as many recipes use this simple ingredient.
Dish of raw Rainbow Trout that keeps the fish’s mana-restoring and elemental resistance attributes.

Odorous paste which restores your maximum health and stamina, allowing you to continue adventuring without sleep.
It also instantly cures infections.
Filling but ordinary dish made with whatever meat and plants are at hand, with a pinch of salt.
Superior egg and fish dish with healing properties which restore health, stamina and mana.
Special dish of the Chersonese which restores a fair amount of stamina and a large amount of health.

Mushrooms pounded into a bar shape.
It restores a bit of maximum health.
Salted fish soup is more restorative and nutritious than fish alone.
Chunky soup that has mana-restoring properties, and will slowly heal the common cold.
Filling omelet that is a good way to use Common Mushrooms to cook into a decent dish.
Hardened exotic egg that rots more slowly than its raw counterpart.

Pearlbird egg boiled over a campfire, removing the risk of disease.
Eggs provide both health and stamina recovery over time.
Gaberry jam thinly spread on bread, used to multiply the effects of jam into several portions.
Boiled fruit that provides a bit of nutrition and rots more slowly.

Boiled root that increased its mana-restoring properties.
It is no longer reinvigorating, however.
Crumbling fungus that barely provides nutrition.
Iridescent steak of a rare bird that increases one’s movement speed.

Boiled octopus that is less toxic but with lower restorative qualities.
It also instantly cures infections.
Tender fruit, boiled to reveal its anti-poison properties.
Mushy fruit that, after being boiled, offers an immediate jolt of stamina.

Special dish of the Hallowed Marsh that immediately heals wounds, unlike most food.
It also gives the Possessed boon.
Elaborate stew using alpha meat and a gravel beetle, which gives Impact Resistance as well as adding Impact to one’s attacks with the Rage status.

Translucent spread of delicious fruit jam.
The concentrated melon confers an immense stamina recovery.
Melon jelly thinly spread on bread, making several rations, each with the full stamina-restoring properties of a jar of marshmellon jam.

Fire-infused plant, seared again in fire.
It will slowly remove the common cold with its heat.
Crudely cooked mushroom that, when eaten, muffles the sound of one’s footsteps.

Burnt slice of bread.
It fills the belly, but does little else.
Special dish of Abrassar, allowing one to run fast and without pause.

Thorny dessert with high health and stamina restorative properties.
It also helps against the sun when eaten.
Dish of invigorating cactus fruit and bread that helps against the heat when eaten.

Special dish of Enmerkar that is unequaled in healing wounds over time.
It also grants the Warm boon and an increase in stealth.
Medicinal mushroom dish that removes poison and diseases.
Mixture of vegetables and mushrooms that heals a bit, but can fill an empty stomach.
Cooked crustacean coveted for its mana-restoring qualities.

Bland biscuit used when traveling from one region to the next, though it can be eaten as normal food as well.
This food with no properties apart from being filling, and can even be made using Survival Crafting.
Roasted nut that increases the metabolism.
Seed that becomes more toxic after being cooked and can be crafted, using linen, into a poisonous weapon coating.
Soup which restores stamina and increases the physical damage one deals to foes.
Alcoholic drink that makes one unstable on their feet, but reduces the mana cost of spells.

Drinking water restores stamina over time and removes the Burning status.
It can be filled at fountains or in natural bodies of water.
Concoction that instantly cures infections, protects against the cold and restores burnt Stamina.

Concoction that cures the common cold and restores burnt Mana.
It takes hours, after drinking this, to fully recover from the cold.

Concoction that helps with the heat and indigestion. It also restores burnt Stamina.
It takes hours, after drinking this, to fully recover from an indigestion.

Concoction that increases Impact Resistance and cures indigestion. It also restores burnt Health.
It takes hours, after drinking this, to fully recover from an indigestion.
Potion which instantly heals some wounds.
Potion which instantly restores some mana.

Potion which instantly reinvigorates a tired body.
It restores a bit of max stamina.
Brew that restores a moderate amount of health, stamina and mana.
Concoction that temporarily increases your weapon’s Impact.
Concoction that temporarily increases your Physical Damage.
Concoction that temporarily increases your Fire Damage and Resistances.
Concoction that temporarily increases your Frost Damage and Resistances.
Concoction that temporarily increases your Ethereal Damage and Resistances.
Concoction that temporarily increases your Lightning Damage and Resistances.

Brew that neutralizes most poisons.
Notably, the toxic effect of the Hallowed Marsh’s waters cannot be cured by this potion.
Strange brew that neutralizes the Hallowed Marsh’s poison, but not other toxins.
Concoction that temporarily increases your Decay Damage and Resistances.
Brew that temporary increases your stealth, making enemies less aware of your presence.
Powerful concoction that temporarily grants moderate resistance against Fire, Frost, Lightning, Decay and Ethereal damage.
Legendary brew that temporarily grants immunity to Fire, Frost, Lightning, Decay and Ethereal damage.

Concoction that provides relief from warm and cold temperatures.
Note that it has no effect on Fire and Frost damage.
Concoction that increases your Impact Resistance.
Powerful concoction that temporarily increases your movement speed, stealth and coats your equipped melee weapon with poison.

Strange brew that removes most negative effects.
Has no effect on Bleeding, Poison, Disease and Burning.
Powerful concoction that temporarily increases your Impact Resistance and the Physical Damage your attacks deal and grants the Rage boon.
Powerful concoction that temporarily increases the Physical Damage and Impact your attacks deal dealt and grants the Discipline boon.
Powerful concoction that restores stamina and burnt stamina, and provides protection from hot and freezing environments.
Powerful concoction that temporarily increases your weapon’s Impact and gives you the Possessed and the Discipline boons.

Concoction which instantly restores health and max health.
It also closes Bleeding wounds.
Concoction which instantly restores mana and max mana.
Concoction which instantly restores stamina and max stamina.
Potion that grants permanent bonuses to the one who drinks it.
Band of thick linen cloth used to stop a bleeding wound and recover a bit of health.
Soiled cloth that envenoms a weapon when rubbed on it.
Thick fluid that envenoms a weapon when applied to it.
Soiled cloth that confers the Lightning element when rubbed on a melee weapon.
Thick fluid that confers the Lightning element when applied to a melee weapon.
Soiled cloth that confers the Fire element when rubbed on a melee weapon.

Thick fluid that confers the Fire element when applied to a melee weapon.

Soiled cloth that confers the Frost element when rubbed on a melee weapon.

Thick fluid that confers the Frost element when applied to a melee weapon.
The weapon will also inflict Slow Down to enemies.
Thick fluid that confers the Ethereal element when applied to a melee weapon.
Thick fluid that confers the Decay element when applied to a melee weapon.

Ammunition for pistols, crafted from iron and oil.
Pistol skills often still require bullets.

Well-made tent that helps protect against the weather, compared to a bedroll.

Primitive bedding made from leather, which offers poor sleep quality.

Minimalist tent that conceals the user, reducing the chances of being ambushed.

Highly visible silk tent that offers high sleep quality, quickly healing the user.
Sleeping in this tent gives a huge bonus to stamina use.
Quality tent that, when slept in, helps the efficiency of one’s spells.

Wondrous shelter born of a seed, which protects against the heat and refills one’s thirst and hunger.

Deployable fire kit that must then be lit, usually with a flint and steel.

Tools used to distill ingredients into potions, to be used on a lit campfire.

Device that must be armed with a compatible item, then triggered by an enemy.

Crushed marsh insects that emit a luminous haze, used in some alchemical recipes.
Rare plants that grow on mountains and used in alchemy.
Phosphorescent leaves with alchemical properties.
Spectral remains used in ethereal-related alchemical recipes.
Algae that, when infused in water in a cooking pot, produces an indigestion-curing tea.

Handful of salt, obtained by mining rock or boiling sea water over a campfire.
It is essential in cooking and in alchemy.
Branches with a variety of uses, from making campfires to crafting weapons.
Shimmering gem that glimmers with shining power.

Beautiful one-of-a-kind gem formed in the heart of a unique horror.
It is a memento from a hard-fought battle to save the city of Monsoon.

Fossilized shells of ancient sea creatures.
These iridescent stones are used to craft Ammolite Armor.

Ancient resin that can be shaped into armors.
Only the smiths of the city of Berg possess such techniques, though.

Semiprecious stone found near water, unlike other gems.
It can fetch a decent price.

Hefty precious stone with a lush green color.
It can fetch an enormous price.

Tiny precious stone with a royal blue color.
It can fetch a good price.

Moderately sized precious stone with a burning red color.
It can fetch a high price.

Dark gem with intricate magical properties.
Craftsmen in Levant can create wizardly robes from this material.

Complex array of metals, made by Levant artisants, to power machines such as the Water Purifier in Cierzo.
A few prototype lanterns were built to use a coil as a power source, but they proved too expensive for mass production.

Carved idol, infused with Blue Sand.
The venerable ancestors would be satisfied with this opulent gift.

Valuable metal ingot used to easily transport wealth.
It has no practical use but every merchant will buy such ingots at the same fixed price.

Irregular lump of high quality metal, used to craft exotic arms and armors.
Crafting monster weapons often requires this material, as iron is often insufficient.
Mineral component used by the blacksmiths of Berg to craft an unusual set of armor.

Glittering powder used by blacksmiths to craft armors made of blue steel alloy.
It is also highly prized as a alchemical ingredient.
Unrefined mineral that radiates raw magic, used in many alchemical recipes.

Pieces of iron, obtained by mining or decrafting metal objects.
Decrafting using the “Manual Recipe” of the Survival Crafting menu.
Transmuted Mana Stone, using an Alchemy Kit to merge the stone and oil.
Transmuted Mana Stone, using an Alchemy Kit to merge the stone and a pinch of Blue Sand.

Roll of fabric commonly used in basic crafting recipes, such as bandages.
Basic clothes can be decrafted, using the Survival Crafting menu, into linen.
Spikes that must be placed in a Tripwire Trap, inflicting damage to enemies that step on it.
Spikes that must be placed in a Tripwire Trap, inflicting heavy damage to enemies that step on it.
Explosives that, when placed in a Pressure Plate, inflict lingering fire damage to enemies that step on it.
Vials that, when placed in a Pressure Plate, inflict lingering decay damage to enemies that step on it.
Gas bladder that, when placed in a Pressure Plate, inflicts Ethereal Damage and Pain to enemies that step on it.
Spikes that must be placed in a Tripwire Trap, inflicting low damage to enemies that step on it.
Tanned animal skin, used in many basic crafting recipes.
Sturdy hide obtained by skinning scaled beasts, used in advanced crafting recipes.

Refined mana crystal used to craft powerful equipment.
Consuming this powder restores mana, burnt mana and burnt stamina. However, it burns maximum health until one sleeps again.
Assortment of fangs, used to craft equipment by binding them to iron weapons.
Antler of a Coralhorn male, used to craft strong bows.
Flammable fluid used to refuel lanterns and to make incendiary weapons.
Dried shell with few uses but that can be sold at a good price.
Massive claw of a rock mantis, used to craft weapons.
Dry remnants of necrotic beings, used in alchemy and to craft weapons.
Wondrous shell from the mightiest horrors, used to craft extremely powerful weapons.

Odd remnants of a unique Shell Horror, proving the beast was slain.
This chitin is too unstable to be of use for crafting weapons.
Finely wrought blades from a beast golem’s jaw, used to craft weapons.
Bony spurs harvested from lesser horrors, used to craft weapons.
Spiked tail, filled with venom, used to craft powerful weapons.
Poisonous bones of large herbivores, used to craft spears.
Flexible tissue of a crescent shark, used to craft fast Ethereal weapons.
Venomous tongue of a giant insect, used to craft swords.
Circular tail bone of an apex predator, used to craft powerful axes.
Chunk of fire-infused glass, used to craft bludgeoning weapons.
Box of golden gears, used to craft a wide variety of weapons.
Large mineralized heart of an Ash Giant.

Bundle of goods.
Someone else may have a use for these supplies.

Universal currency of the land.
Note that a hundred coins have a combined weight of 1.

A great hunter’s knife that emits light.
This off-hand weapon requires Dagger Skills to be used.
Fabled book used to cast runic spells with greater efficiency.

Fueled by an advanced Power Coil, this lantern provides light for an extremely long time.
The coil can be swapped for a new one when the light does run out.

Bag containing the arcane talismans collected long ago by an undead wizard.
<color=#ff5043>Equipping this backpack slows your dodge.</color>
A small key that can unlock certain doors.

Trophy-laden bag of the great hunter Zhorn, who used it to trek across vast distances.
<color=#ff5043>Equipping this backpack slows your dodge.</color>
